        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 4:19PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 419 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Milliken, or 11 miles southwest of Greeley, moving northeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Greeley, Evans, Johnstown, Milliken, LaSalle, Gilcrest, Garden
City, Peckham, Fort St Vrain and Lower Latham Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
